text.section:
An application for licensure as an elevator contractor shall contain the following:
For an applicant who is a person or sole proprietor:
Name;
Residence; and
Business address of the applicant;
For an applicant that is a partnership:
Names of the partners;
Residential addresses of the partners; and
Business address of the partnership;
For an applicant that is a domestic corporation:
Name of the principal corporate officer;
Residential address of the principal corporate officer; and
Business address of the corporation;
For an applicant that is a corporation other than a domestic corporation:
Name of the corporation's agent who is authorized to accept service of process and official notices on behalf of the corporation in the state; and
Physical address of the corporation's authorized agent;
The number of years the applicant has engaged in the business of installing, maintaining, or servicing elevators or fixed guideway systems;
The approximate number of persons, if any, to be employed by the elevator contractor applicant;
Proof that he or she has complied with workers' compensation and unemployment insurance laws;
Evidence that the applicant is covered by general liability, personal injury, and property damage insurance;
Criminal record of convictions, if any, as verified through a criminal background check conducted by the Department of Kentucky State Police. The cost of the background check shall be paid by the applicant; and
Upon request by the department, supplemental documentation of information required by this section.
